headline.main: SNAG AGAIN REPORTED IN NAZI-TURK TRADE; Signing of Pact Seems Delayed on Issue of Deliveries

lead_paragraph: ANKARA, Turkey, Oct. 6 -- The Turkish-German trade negotiations struck a second snag today, according to usually well-informed foreign trade and diplomatic circles, and the new Turkish-German trade pact may not be signed until next week or later.
abstract: pact signing delayed by Turkish delivery proposals; Clodius and Menemencioglu conf
